      "description": "Architecture Review: Monolith to Microservices Migration\n\nRFC Document: https://docs.google.com/document/d/abc123\n\nKey Decision Points:\n1. Service boundary definitions — where to split the monolith\n2. Data ownership model — which service owns which data?\n3. Inter-service communication pattern (REST vs gRPC vs event-driven)\n4. Migration strategy (strangler fig vs big bang)\n\nRequired Attendees:\n- Marcus Johnson (Engineering Manager) — decision authority\n- Alice Wong (Senior Engineer) — architecture proposal author\n- Bob Kumar (Backend Lead) — implementation lead\n- Chen Mei (DevOps) — infrastructure planning\n\nPre-read:\n- RFC document (link above)\n- Current monolith dependency graph\n- AWS cost projection for microservices architecture\n\nDecision: Service boundaries and data ownership MUST be finalized in this meeting to unblock Sprint 25 planning.",
